      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get what you're saying about regulations but what if it's not at the platform level? like what if someone is intercepting the signal or using something like a man-in-the-middle attack to inject these frequencies into my local stream? it would be so much harder to track if it was happening at the device or network level rather than the spotify servers themselves. do you think there are ways to \"cleanse\" my audio or scan for those specific sub-bass patterns to be sure i'm actually just hearing the song?",
